<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: I really need some warrior questions answered</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?scz">scz</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 4:55 p.m. 8/7/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: I really need some warrior questions answered<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/forum/innoruuk.cgi?read=237" TARGET=_self>I really need some warrior questions answered</A> (Filthy McNasty)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>Trolls regen HP faster and have better Dexterity. Ogres are stronger. I hit as hard as any Ogre out there at my level. Since strength seems to have little to no bearing on damage, I like the Troll. But either one for a melee class would be fine.

<BR>Just keep in mind that you will be killed on sight in 75% of the zones in the game, and things like boat rides are much more difficult, since you can't use the docks because of the guards. I would suggest (IMHO) that your first character NOT be an evil race (Troll, Ogre, Dark Elf) or an evil class (Necromancer, Shadow Knight). Once you have gotten the fundamentals out of the game (Play to L9 or so with a "good" character"), then feel free to try the other combinations.
<BR>I started with a human Wizard, and it made it easier to survive as an evil race with my Troll and my Dark Elf Necro later.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
